From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] wifi: mt76: mt7921: enable CLC for USB (experimental)

The mt7921_load_clc() function returns 0 immediately for USB devices
at mcu.c:425-427, blocking 6 GHz band operation and leaving 2.4/5 GHz
without country-specific power limits. Without CLC data, the firmware
has no regulatory domain information, and clc_chan_conf remains at
0xff (all UNII bits enabled) without actual jurisdiction-specific
power reduction.

This creates both a feature gap (no 6 GHz channels) and a regulatory
compliance risk: the device may transmit at power levels exceeding
legal EIRP limits in jurisdictions that require country-specific power
reduction (FCC: 30 dBm, ETSI: 20 dBm, etc.).

Remove the mt76_is_usb() condition from the CLC skip path, allowing
USB devices to load CLC data. This is marked experimental because the
firmware may not accept MCU_CE_CMD(SET_CLC) over USB bulk transport.
If SET_CLC is rejected by the firmware, the retry mechanism from the
preceding patch (max_retry = 3) will attempt multiple times before
falling back to chip reset.

If testing confirms SET_CLC is not viable over USB, the alternative
path is to port the vendor driver's regulatory mechanism
(CMD_ID_CAL_BACKUP_IN_HOST_V2 + rlmDomainGetChnlList()), which uses
an entirely different command interface for USB regulatory
configuration.

The module parameter disable_clc remains available as a safety
override.

Fixes: 967a4ff41e4e ("mt76: mt7921: introduce mt7921u support")
Signed-off-by: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mcu.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mcu.c b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mcu.c
index 1234567..abcdef6 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mcu.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mcu.c
@@ -424,8 +424,7 @@ static int mt7921_load_clc(struct mt792x_dev *dev, const char *fw_name)
 	u8 *clc_base = NULL, hw_encap = 0;

 	dev->phy.clc_chan_conf = 0xff;
-	if (mt7921_disable_clc ||
-	    mt76_is_usb(&dev->mt76))
+	if (mt7921_disable_clc)
 		return 0;

 	if (mt76_is_mmio(&dev->mt76)) {

